Communicable Scale:
Def: A model of designation about comparing an activity through oral descriptions. 

A communicable scale is a by definition a tool used to describe a situation and or event in numerical or graphical data.
Example: “Joseph has traveled 50% of his 26 hour journey between Florida and Maine.”
Compared to “Joseph is in the middle of his trip”
